message: added one description on current role
/* Arrest and conviction */ - correct information from website on no disciplinary action.
/* Arrest and conviction */ - trial summary documents make clear no child was harmed - the title of news article is misleading

/* Arrest and conviction */ - there is no disciplinary action on the website which is clearly stated and the license goes inactive when a physician moves out of state. It is important that information is accurate and not misleading

first part is repetitive on person and inaccurate.  He resigned before being convicted.  The conviction was child endangerment.  No child was injured as documented multiple times at trial and in the public record.

The child charges were part of the DUI conviction, which included an aggravating charge for child endangerment.  No child was harmed during the incident as was proven in the trial which was recorded and documented.  Dr. Conway still serves as a pediatrician and no disciplinary actions were taken by the medical board. He also publicly stated in the Wall Street Journal his apology for the incident.
despite reporting of "child abuse", no child was injured as documented in court proceedings and the actual legal conviction was for child endangerment.

Dr. Conway had an unrestricted license with no disciplinary action and ability to practice medicine during his entire time in North Carolina.  His license became inactive when he moved to MA.  He currently still has an unrestricted license to practice medicine in MA.
/* Arrest and conviction */Added sentence with citation
